1
00:01:56,780 --> 00:02:00,700
- Walk the wall on the left!
- I need a line!

2
00:02:07,220 --> 00:02:11,940
I found her!
I found her!

3
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:13,860
I need some help
down here!

4
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:18,860
I need it now!

5
00:02:18,980 --> 00:02:21,940
Anybody hear me?

6
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:24,780
Get down here now!

7
00:02:24,820 --> 00:02:26,700
Come on!

8
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:34,100
Shepherd! Burr!

9
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:36,740
I got her! I can't move!

10
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:39,980
Come down here now!

11
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:43,980
Hold on.
They'll be here.

12
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:46,540
Move!

13
00:02:48,180 --> 00:02:50,700
- I heard a voice.
- Help me!

14
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:54,340
I can't breathe!

15
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:59,060
Help me! Help me out!
Help me out!

16
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:02,180
Help me move it!

17
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:32,220
Bring up the skycam.
Pan it left.

18
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:34,620
Show me what God sees.

19
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:38,780
Okay, camera two, show me the stands.

20
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:41,100
- Three, give me the ice.
- Okay, graphic is up.

21
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:43,060
Uh, put game seven on preset.

22
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:45,500
How many technicians
are gonna be inside the arena?

23
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:47,820
We got 12 cameramen,
6 support... that's 18.

24
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,780
I want to limit their access.

25
00:03:49,820 --> 00:03:52,140
Technicians and announcers
are the only ones cleared.

26
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:54,420
Hey, Spota, let us in.

27
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:57,820
Work don't stop just 'cause the
Vice President's coming, you know, babe.

28
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:59,740
Must be Republicans.

29
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:02,140
Having everybody check in through one
gate like this is a pain in the butt.

30
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:04,540
- It's only one night.
- It's the last game of the Stanley Cup.

31
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:07,060
Having the Vice President
here turns a headache into a concussion.

32
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:10,660
- I didn't vote for this guy.
- That's what makes what you're
doin' such a special gesture.

33
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:22,540
Hello, Pittsburgh.

34
00:04:22,580 --> 00:04:26,380
Here we are in the seventh game of the
Stanley Cup finals. Penguins and Hawks.

35
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:30,100
Penguins in a come-from-behind
victory to shut down the Hawks.

36
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:33,620
Shit.

37
00:04:36,620 --> 00:04:39,260
Sorry. Uh, my dog's missing.

38
00:04:39,380 --> 00:04:41,220
We're out looking for him.

39
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:44,620
- Is it bad?
- What? You think this might be good?

40
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,780
- Let me see your license.
- Oh, sure.

41
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:49,060
Move. Move.

42
00:04:49,180 --> 00:04:51,500
We are going to steal your car.

43
00:04:51,580 --> 00:04:54,220
Don't get killed over it, huh?

44
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:23,660
It's the last game.
We got a couple of minutes to go.

45
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:25,340
Just 15 seconds to go!

46
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:28,100
He skates up to center.
He knocks down one defender.

47
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:31,340
He's skating like a madman around
the ice. He gets to the blue line.

48
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:34,340
He shoots. Whoa!
And he scores! Whoo!

49
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:37,940
- Scratch my back with a hacksaw...
- Yes!

50
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:39,980
Dad!

51
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:41,540
Hey!

52
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:45,860
- That's a fancy new stick.
- Michael gave it to me.

53
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:48,140
- Hi.
- How are you, Darren?

54
00:05:48,180 --> 00:05:50,220
Darren, what are you
doing here?

55
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:53,260
- You can't stay.
We're getting ready to leave.
- It's his birthday.

56
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:55,540
And you've got him
all day tomorrow.

57
00:05:55,660 --> 00:05:58,580
I just got these.
I thought the kids might wanna...

58
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:01,580
We're all going out
to dinner.

59
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:05,780
- Looks like those are Penguin tickets.
- They are.

60
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,620
It's the seventh game.

61
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,700
- Vice President's gonna be there.
- Daddy! Daddy!

62
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:15,420
- Hey, that's my hat!
- I can wear it. Mom said I could.

63
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,340
I did?

64
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:20,620
You know what that means?

65
00:06:22,820 --> 00:06:25,580
- Not a clue.
- It means "I love you."

66
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:29,460
I love you too.

67
00:06:29,540 --> 00:06:32,660
She's practicing to be deaf,
but that's still my hat!

68
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:36,820
- I'll get you a new one.
- You can't just take them
without talking to me first.

69
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:39,940
- Besides, you only have two tickets.
- I'm working at the arena.

70
00:06:40,020 --> 00:06:43,380
- You're back to work, Dad?
- He's a fire inspector at the game.

71
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:46,740
- It's very important work.
- Are you a fireman again, Daddy?

72
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:50,060
Kind of, yeah.

73
00:06:50,140 --> 00:06:52,020
Kathi tells me it's only temporary.

74
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:56,660
- He was trying to save a little
girl in a burning building...
- Are we going to the game?

75
00:06:59,140 --> 00:07:01,020
Don't do this again. I mean it.

76
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:04,100
It's not fair to the kids... or me.

77
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:06,060
I promise.

78
00:08:44,940 --> 00:08:47,220
Excuse me.

79
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:04,500
This is Andrew.
He's the head chef.

80
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:06,660
Nobody goes in that elevator,
and I mean nobody,

81
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:09,300
even if they have proper I.D.,
unless this man says it's okay.

82
00:09:09,420 --> 00:09:11,500
If he doesn't know them,
they don't get in that elevator.

83
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:14,980
After you finish the Vice President's
party, this kitchen is closed.

84
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:17,100
- Have I made myself clear?
- Abundantly.

85
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:19,700
That's how I like it.
Abundantly.

86
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:45,740
Mrs. Ferrara?

87
00:09:45,820 --> 00:09:47,700
Yes?

88
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:51,180
Let's just stroll into your house
like I'm your favorite nephew.

89
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:10,740
- Ackerman, Ekers.
- Yeah.

90
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:14,620
Come on, Mac. Mr. McCord makes sure
the building doesn't burn down.

91
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:18,460
Go on through, Mr. Mac.
And who's this beauty?

92
00:10:18,540 --> 00:10:20,700
This is my daughter Emily
and my son Tyler.

93
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:24,180
- Want a stamp?
- Love a stamp.

94
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:27,420
Hey, can you guys play
after we get in?

95
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,900
Hey, hold your horses.
I'm getting a stamp here.

96
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:33,300
I'll never wash
this hand again.

97
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:36,500
- See you later, Mr. Mac.
- Okay.

98
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:50,060
- Joan.
- Hi, Darren.

99
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:53,580
- Are you working tonight?
- After I take Tyler to the locker room.

100
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:56,460
Hey, could you give Emily
a look at Icey?

101
00:10:56,500 --> 00:11:00,300
Icey always loves company. Come on,
Emily, I'm gonna show you where Icey is.

102
00:11:00,420 --> 00:11:03,980
Icey. Big deal.
Some fat guy in a ratty penguin suit.

103
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:07,740
That blonde you're staring at,
she's the fat guy.

104
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:14,060
- What's he doing?
- Shaping the blade.

105
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:17,380
They're like horseshoes. You get 'em
hot enough, you can bend 'em.

106
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:20,300
You, uh, recognize him?

107
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:23,180
Yeah. Luc Robitaille.

108
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,900
He waved at me.
You see that, Dad?

109
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:27,860
Luc Robitaille waved at me.

110
00:11:27,980 --> 00:11:30,220
Come on, I'll introduce you.
He won't bite.

111
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:34,900
- Luc, this is Tyler McCord
and his father Darren.
- Hi, Tyler. How are you?

112
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:36,820
- Ca va?
- Bonjour.

113
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,380
Dad, what did he say?

114
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:47,300
He thinks, uh, they're gonna win.

115
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:50,180
Hey, that's Brad Tolliver!

116
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,460
- Dad, he doesn't have a rocking chair.
- A what?

117
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:55,340
My dad said you should be sitting in
a rocking chair instead of on the ice.

118
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:58,540
- Oh, is that so?
- You play hockey, Tyler?

119
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:01,020
No, but my dad played.
He was a goalie.

120
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:04,620
A little semi-pro in Canada.
It was a long time ago.

121
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:06,580
Come by some afternoon.

122
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,260
I'll show you the difference between
the game you played and the one I play.

123
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:09,860
I'll show you the difference between
the game you played and the one I play.

124
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:12,780
I can see the difference.

125
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:31,260
I got this one, man.

126
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,980
Yes.

127
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:39,780
You boys have fun?

128
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:43,020
Luc Robitaille talked to me,
and we saw Brad Tolliver close up.

129
00:12:43,140 --> 00:12:45,260
Your friends are gonna
be so jealous of you.

130
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,660
- I wanna go with Icey.
- So does Tyler.

131
00:12:47,660 --> 00:12:50,540
Icey has to hit the stands, guys.
I'll see you later.

132
00:12:50,540 --> 00:12:52,460
Bye-bye.

133
00:12:57,260 --> 00:13:00,460
Andrew, this is Emily and Tyler.

134
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,580
Pleasure.

135
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:05,860
- Be right back.
- Come. I want to show you something.

136
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:13,100
Whoa! Cool!

137
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:15,740
That's why you won't hear
anyone complain about my cooking.

138
00:13:15,820 --> 00:13:18,380
- At least not to my face.
- You got a burnt-out light bulb.

139
00:13:18,460 --> 00:13:21,540
Could you change it?
I've got my hands full.

140
00:13:21,620 --> 00:13:23,460
Sure.

141
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:27,020
Is that what Daddy does,
change light bulbs?

142
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:30,180
No, Emily.
He's just helping out.

143
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:33,580
- Firemen don't do that kind of stuff.
- What kind of stuff?

144
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:36,420
- Uh, nothing.
- When are we gonna sit down?

145
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:05,220
Frequent Flyer is in and on
his way to the locker room.

146
00:14:05,260 --> 00:14:07,140
Keep him moving.

147
00:14:14,820 --> 00:14:17,740
The Penguin fans are anxious
to see for the first time...

148
00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:21,540
- the Penguins kicking the Stanley Cup...
- Do you have any cookies?

149
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:24,780
You force your way in here with a gun,
and now I have to feed you?

150
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:28,140
You don't have to.
But I still have the gun.

151
00:14:30,380 --> 00:14:32,580
I think I have some Fig Newtons.

152
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:41,100
Hey! Caution.

153
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:43,220
Caution keeps you safe.

154
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:56,940
I keep my machine gun
in with the produce.

155
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,540
Okay, Veep's comin' in.
Let's get decent!

156
00:14:59,580 --> 00:15:01,580
Christ, Jefferson,
it's a locker room.

157
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:04,780
Duckerman, why don't you
put on a jock?

158
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:07,420
- Got any tape?
- You're covering the right head.

159
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:09,820
Let's go, let's go.

160
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:13,980
All right, guys, I'm privileged to
introduce Vice President Daniel Bender.

161
00:15:14,060 --> 00:15:17,540
He's a big hockey fan
and he'd like to say a few words.

162
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:20,460
"A few words."
There's an optimist.

163
00:15:20,580 --> 00:15:23,180
I want to wish you all
the best of luck and, uh,

164
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:25,380
are you Democrats
or Republicans?

165
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:27,580
Neither, sir. Canadians.

166
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:30,660
Well, in that case, good luck...

167
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:33,540
and I hope to toast
your championship after the game.

168
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:36,580
Sir, are you going to say the
same thing to the Blackhawks?

169
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:39,420
Of course.
Nice outfit, Duckerman.

170
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:52,940
Two nights ago with the Blackhawks
on the brink of elimination...

171
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:55,660
It's time!

172
00:15:55,740 --> 00:15:58,380
I want you to pick up the phone...

173
00:15:58,460 --> 00:16:03,300
and dial 555-1793.

174
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:07,380
- That's my husband's work number.
- It certainly is.

175
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:10,980
When you get him on the line,

176
00:16:11,060 --> 00:16:14,900
- say only what's written on this.
- Ohh.

177
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:20,980
Kitchen. Yeah. Hold on.

178
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:22,900
Andrew, it's your wife.

179
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:33,540
- Hello?
- Andy, it...

180
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:36,300
We have your wife.
Follow her instructions.

181
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:44,020
They will not hurt me...

182
00:16:44,140 --> 00:16:45,940
if you do as they say.

183
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:50,660
If you give any indication something
is wrong, they will... kill me.

184
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:59,220
When you go to the...
Vice President's box,

185
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:02,900
you will take two new
assistants with you...

186
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:05,060
escorted by
two security men.

187
00:17:05,140 --> 00:17:08,660
Get them into the box.
That's all you need to do.

188
00:17:08,780 --> 00:17:11,060
That's all you need to know.

189
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:13,780
Who are these men?
How will I know them?

190
00:17:13,860 --> 00:17:16,660
In 30 seconds, you'll know.

191
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:19,140
I swear this.
If you hurt my wife, I'll...

192
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:22,500
You'll what?
Burn my toast?

193
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,860
- Mr. Ferrara?
- Yes?

194
00:17:33,940 --> 00:17:35,460
Are these men yours?

195
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:45,060
Yes. They're mine.

196
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:53,220
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

197
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:58,260
The National Hockey League presents
game seven of the Stanley Cup finals.

198
00:17:58,340 --> 00:18:02,900
The Chicago Blackhawks
and the Pittsburgh Penguins.

199
00:18:04,940 --> 00:18:07,980
As we get ready for the seventh and
final game of the Stanley Cup finals,

200
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:11,420
you can feel the electricity in the air;
it sends a chill up your spine, Paul.

201
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:15,140
One of these clubs is going to
skate with Lord Stanley's cup
here at Civic Arena Ice tonight.

202
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:20,340
Listen to the crowd, Mike.
They're going crazy.

203
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:22,700
Well, here's to a great game.

204
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:27,380
Great if we win;
not so great if we lose.

205
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:42,020
We are ready.

206
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:45,100
Thank you, everybody.
You may leave now.

207
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:47,060
Mr. Ferrara will close up
your stations.

208
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:59,540
...singing of our National Anthem.

209
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:05,380
Oh, say, can you see

210
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:09,580
# By the dawn's
early light

211
00:19:09,620 --> 00:19:13,700
# What so proudly we hailed

212
00:19:13,740 --> 00:19:17,860
# At the twilight's
last gleaming

213
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:20,420
- # Whose broad stripes
- What the hell are you...

214
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,980
# And bright stars

215
00:19:23,060 --> 00:19:27,500
# Through the perilous fight

216
00:19:27,540 --> 00:19:32,180
# O'er the ramparts
we watched

217
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:36,980
# Were so gallantly streaming

218
00:19:37,060 --> 00:19:41,260
# And the rockets'
red glare

219
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:46,460
# The bombs bursting in air

220
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:51,140
# Gave proof
through the night

221
00:19:51,180 --> 00:19:56,580
# That our flag
was still there

222
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:59,500
- I love that part.
- # Oh, say does that

223
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:02,060
- # Star-spangled
- Well, gotta go.

224
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:08,420
# Banner yet wave

225
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:12,220
# O'er the land

226
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:15,180
# Of the free

227
00:20:15,260 --> 00:20:17,780
# And the home

228
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:22,180
# Of the brave

229
00:20:31,860 --> 00:20:33,740
This place is going crazy right now.

230
00:20:33,780 --> 00:20:37,580
You could not beg, borrow or
steal a ticket before the game tonight.

231
00:20:37,620 --> 00:20:39,620
If you were packing heat,
you couldn't get in here.

232
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:42,180
Eddie Belfour
starts in goal for Chicago.

233
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:44,180
Amazingly, Brad Tolliver will play...

234
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:47,340
even though he could hardly walk today
much less skate with a fever of 104.

235
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:49,940
And here we go.
Game seven of the Stanley Cup finals.

236
00:20:50,060 --> 00:20:52,580
And the Chicago Blackhawks
control the opening face-off.

237
00:20:52,620 --> 00:20:55,940
They'll work into Pittsburgh territory,
putting pressure on the Penguins early.

238
00:20:56,020 --> 00:20:58,060
Graham, slap shot!
Tolliver makes the save.

239
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:03,860
Please, he needs a doctor.

240
00:21:03,940 --> 00:21:06,020
No!

241
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:08,940
Not any more. Go ahead.

242
00:21:09,020 --> 00:21:11,180
