With each stop,
cash is siphoned and rerouted,

711
01:02:58,260 --> 01:03:00,300
some converted to foreign currency,

712
01:03:00,420 --> 01:03:02,980
some to negotiable instruments.

713
01:03:03,100 --> 01:03:05,860
Thanks to the incredibly vast
and complicated world of banking...

714
01:03:05,900 --> 01:03:09,060
that our CIA uses to such advantage,

715
01:03:09,180 --> 01:03:13,540
about 500 million dollars will be lost,
absorbed by the system.

716
01:03:13,660 --> 01:03:17,380
And the other billion,
200 million is just a diversion.

717
01:03:17,420 --> 01:03:20,100
I only wanted enough to
pay off my American Express.

718
01:03:20,140 --> 01:03:22,500
You wouldn't be so generous
with that information...

719
01:03:22,580 --> 01:03:25,380
if you weren't planning
to kill everyone here.

720
01:03:26,940 --> 01:03:30,900
Who gets the Cup if I blow up
the building before the game is over?

721
01:03:34,860 --> 01:03:36,660
Yeah?

722
01:03:38,460 --> 01:03:41,260
Not on the phone. You know
they've got the frequency by now.

723
01:03:47,980 --> 01:03:49,780
Don't go away.

724
01:03:51,820 --> 01:03:55,220
Taken away, and McEachern
hustling down the right side.

725
01:03:55,300 --> 01:03:59,340
Coming into the Chicago end. Moves in to
the net. A backhand shot, off-target.

726
01:04:16,420 --> 01:04:19,180
McCord's disarming your bombs.

727
01:04:19,220 --> 01:04:22,020
- Is he guessing?
- He's a pretty good guesser.

728
01:04:22,100 --> 01:04:23,940
- Is he alone?
- Yeah.

729
01:04:24,020 --> 01:04:27,820
- Why didn't you kill him?
- Two of your goons started
firing at us. He ran off.

730
01:04:27,860 --> 01:04:32,300
- It was all I could do to keep
from getting my own ass shot.
- I want him.

731
01:04:32,420 --> 01:04:35,180
I would've had him if you had
more control over your men.

732
01:04:35,300 --> 01:04:38,940
The only problem my men had is they
didn't hit what they were shooting at.

733
01:04:39,020 --> 01:04:41,820
Look, I was there too.

734
01:04:43,100 --> 01:04:44,860
Nice.

735
01:04:46,620 --> 01:04:49,420
I got the next best thing
to the fireman.

736
01:04:49,500 --> 01:04:53,260
He's got a little boy here in the arena.
I know where he's sitting.

737
01:04:53,380 --> 01:04:55,460
Bring him to me.

738
01:04:56,660 --> 01:04:58,820
I always wanted a son.

739
01:05:02,580 --> 01:05:05,020
Greg Smyth against Robitaille,
and zoom!

740
01:05:05,100 --> 01:05:09,740
Quick shot, save made! Hawgood trying
to tee it up. Stopped by Tolliver.

741
01:05:13,020 --> 01:05:15,580
- Tyler?
- Yeah?

742
01:05:15,660 --> 01:05:17,820
Pretty exciting game, huh?

743
01:05:17,900 --> 01:05:22,660
- How come you know my name?
- Your dad and I are friends.
He asked me to come get you.

744
01:05:22,740 --> 01:05:27,340
He and your sister got invited to sit
in the owner's box, way up there.

745
01:05:27,420 --> 01:05:30,220
They got big soft chairs
and plenty to eat.

746
01:05:30,300 --> 01:05:34,060
My dad told me to stay here,
even if the building fell down.

747
01:05:34,140 --> 01:05:36,940
If it did come down,
up there is where you'd wanna be.

748
01:05:37,020 --> 01:05:39,140
Come on.

749
01:05:39,260 --> 01:05:41,180
I'm gonna stay here.

750
01:05:41,260 --> 01:05:44,300
I'm gonna be embarrassed
going back without you.

751
01:05:46,340 --> 01:05:50,820
- Do you know my mom?
- No, but your dad's invited me
over for dinner tomorrow.

752
01:05:50,860 --> 01:05:53,740
My mom and dad don't live together.

753
01:05:53,860 --> 01:05:56,620
He didn't mention that.
He just said bring you upstairs.

754
01:05:56,740 --> 01:05:59,940
- Don't you think you should
do what you're told?
- I am.

755
01:06:02,380 --> 01:06:05,700
I need you to come with me.
I'm with the Secret Service.

756
01:06:05,740 --> 01:06:08,460
- Come with me now.
- Come on! Down in front!

757
01:06:10,660 --> 01:06:13,500
- I'll scream.
- I said, I'm with the Secret Service.

758
01:06:13,580 --> 01:06:17,660
- And I'm a little kid.
- Hey, fella, I didn't pay to watch you!

759
01:06:17,740 --> 01:06:19,580
Down in front!

760
01:06:27,780 --> 01:06:30,740
Steve Smith finds the lane.
He'll skate ahead.

761
01:06:30,820 --> 01:06:32,460
Coming to the Penguin line.

762
01:07:07,180 --> 01:07:09,220
How many'd you get?

763
01:07:09,300 --> 01:07:12,300
Four, so far.

764
01:07:12,380 --> 01:07:15,180
- Is that all?
- Christ, I'm just one guy.

765
01:07:15,260 --> 01:07:18,060
- How many did you get?
- Just one.

766
01:07:19,380 --> 01:07:22,980
You are all alone, aren't you?

767
01:07:28,300 --> 01:07:31,900
- You must be real proud.
- I'm gonna be real rich.

768
01:07:31,940 --> 01:07:34,300
Now, very slowly...
I mean very slowly...

769
01:07:34,380 --> 01:07:38,180
pull your hands
out of your pockets.

770
01:07:43,380 --> 01:07:47,300
- What are you gonna do, drown me?
- No.

771
01:08:17,820 --> 01:08:19,660
Aaaah!

772
01:09:12,860 --> 01:09:15,180
- Yeah?
- Hallmark's dead.

773
01:09:15,300 --> 01:09:18,140
- Who's this?
- Tom Castillo, Secret Service.

774
01:09:18,220 --> 01:09:22,020
Tom Castillo.
How you doin', Tom?

775
01:09:22,100 --> 01:09:24,540
- I hope you were gentle with Hallmark.
- How many hostages,

776
01:09:24,620 --> 01:09:26,940
besides the Vice President,
are still alive?

777
01:09:27,020 --> 01:09:30,300
That's a personal question.
Ever been involved in an A.O.P., Tom?

778
01:09:30,380 --> 01:09:33,580
I didn't call for conversation.
How many are still alive?

779
01:09:33,700 --> 01:09:37,420
You'd probably think I was lying,
no matter what I told you,

780
01:09:37,540 --> 01:09:41,260
so I'm gonna let you talk
to a little friend of mine.

781
01:09:43,260 --> 01:09:45,540
Hello?

782
01:09:45,620 --> 01:09:48,580
- Hello?
- Emily.

783
01:09:48,660 --> 01:09:52,100
Don't let him know it's me. I'll get
you out. I'll take you home, I promise.

784
01:09:52,140 --> 01:09:55,940
Look around and tell me
how many people are there.

785
01:09:58,860 --> 01:10:01,020
Twelve.

786
01:10:01,060 --> 01:10:03,900
Well, now, wasn't that sweet?

787
01:10:03,980 --> 01:10:06,420
She included me, Tom.

788
01:10:06,540 --> 01:10:09,860
Tell me what an A.O.P. is, or I'm gonna
shoot this cute little pumpkin.

789
01:10:09,980 --> 01:10:12,060
Listen to me. Listen good.

790
01:10:12,100 --> 01:10:15,100
If you touch her,
you look at her cross-eyed, you lose.

791
01:10:15,140 --> 01:10:17,540
How do you figure that, fireman?

792
01:10:17,660 --> 01:10:21,420
Okay, here's the game
and here are the rules.

793
01:10:21,540 --> 01:10:24,580
You've got your hostages and your bombs,
so you can get your money.

794
01:10:24,660 --> 01:10:28,420
I'm gonna try to stop you,
but I don't want anyone to get hurt.

795
01:10:28,500 --> 01:10:30,380
You stop me, you win.
I get your bombs, I win.

796
01:10:30,420 --> 01:10:32,260
You stop me, you win.
I get your bombs, I win.

797
01:10:32,420 --> 01:10:33,460
That's the game,
you piece of shit.

798
01:10:33,540 --> 01:10:37,220
If you touch her, the game's off.
Then I'll come after you.

799
01:10:37,260 --> 01:10:41,420
You'll have to kill me in front of every
body in this arena. There will be panic.

800
01:10:41,500 --> 01:10:45,060
The Secret Service, S.W.A.T., the
fucking navy will have to come in here.

801
01:10:45,180 --> 01:10:47,940
Then you don't get your money.
You lose, pal.

802
01:10:47,980 --> 01:10:50,820
Well, that's not bad
for a civil servant.

803
01:10:50,860 --> 01:10:53,700
Oh, by the way,
in the Secret Service,

804
01:10:53,740 --> 01:10:55,380
A.O.P. is "assault on principle."

805
01:10:55,460 --> 01:10:58,180
- In this case, our Vice President.
- I don't give a shit.

806
01:10:58,180 --> 01:11:02,940
Ooh, now, Tom, come on. If we're
gonna play, you got to play nice.

807
01:11:03,020 --> 01:11:07,780
You run your ass off. I know where the
bombs are, so I know where you're going.

808
01:11:07,860 --> 01:11:10,820
Then come and get me.

809
01:11:12,900 --> 01:11:16,380
Would you like
a glass of wine or a cigarette?

810
01:11:16,420 --> 01:11:20,140
It's customary to offer these
minor vices to someone before they die.

811
01:11:29,740 --> 01:11:32,580
- I'm not afraid of you.
- Sure you are.

812
01:11:32,620 --> 01:11:36,100
- I'm the scariest person you've seen.
- You're the meanest.

813
01:11:36,140 --> 01:11:38,980
Am I, now?
How do you suppose I got that way?

814
01:11:39,020 --> 01:11:43,780
Maybe when you were born
you had something wrong with your brain.

815
01:11:45,740 --> 01:11:48,420
Don't you know any little boys like me?

816
01:11:48,540 --> 01:11:51,460
If there were any at my school,
they'd get expelled.

817
01:11:51,500 --> 01:11:53,740
I can assure you there are one or two.

818
01:11:53,780 --> 01:11:58,340
I'm gonna kill your daddy.
What do you think about that?

819
01:11:58,380 --> 01:12:02,140
He promised he'd take me home.
He always does what he says.

820
01:12:02,220 --> 01:12:03,740
So do I.

821
01:12:12,340 --> 01:12:15,300
We're in the third period.
The Penguins on the rush.

822
01:12:15,420 --> 01:12:17,540
Tamer brings it in.

823
01:12:17,620 --> 01:12:21,060
He puts it in!
Ron Francis!

824
01:12:21,140 --> 01:12:25,700
Oh, buy Sam a drink
and get his dog one too!

825
01:12:48,460 --> 01:12:51,140
Chicago desperate to get
back into this game.

826
01:12:51,220 --> 01:12:55,460
Sutter fires and scores!
Chicago does get the third goal!

827
01:12:55,540 --> 01:12:59,300
I tell ya, Mike, I don't think
Tolliver looks like himself right now.

828
01:12:59,340 --> 01:13:02,540
We shouldn't be surprised. He had
a 104 degree temperature earlier today.

829
01:13:02,620 --> 01:13:05,860
He looks like he's struggling
in that goal for the Penguin.

830
01:13:05,940 --> 01:13:09,260
- Yo, Ref.
- He's calling for the referee.

831
01:13:09,340 --> 01:13:12,580
- He might wanna go to the bench.
- Tolliver is gonna head that way.

832
01:13:12,660 --> 01:13:15,460
- Backup for the Penguins is Ken Wregget.
- What's the matter?

833
01:13:15,540 --> 01:13:19,340
I really feel like shit.
I don't think I can goal.

834
01:13:19,380 --> 01:13:21,940
Go to the locker room. Wregget!

835
01:13:22,020 --> 01:13:24,300
- Get in there.
- Let's go, Kenny.

836
01:13:27,700 --> 01:13:31,780
Now in goal for Pittsburgh,
number 31, Ken Wregget.

837
01:13:42,940 --> 01:13:44,780
Hey, fireman, where are you?

838
01:13:44,860 --> 01:13:47,780
- You don't call, you don't write.
- I'm not far away.

839
01:13:47,860 --> 01:13:50,300
- How many have you found?
- How many what?

840
01:13:50,380 --> 01:13:53,220
I could detonate all ten right now.

841
01:13:53,260 --> 01:13:56,100
Go ahead. Then you lose.

842
01:13:59,980 --> 01:14:02,300
Nervous stomach, fireman?

843
01:14:04,940 --> 01:14:07,300
He's at number seven.
Get somebody there.

844
01:14:12,820 --> 01:14:15,140
Charge!

845
01:14:15,140 --> 01:14:20,260
Roberts cannot get it out.
Chelios in deep. A shot off the stick!

846
01:14:26,580 --> 01:14:28,340
Section B. Now.

847
01:15:44,980 --> 01:15:47,140
Chelios guns it ahead
to Bernie Nicholls.

848
01:15:47,220 --> 01:15:49,700
Here he comes!
Look out!

849
01:15:49,700 --> 01:15:54,140
He shoots and scores! Bernie Nicholls
carried it in, right down the slot.

850
01:15:54,260 --> 01:15:55,780
A heavy slap shot.

851
01:16:03,500 --> 01:16:07,940
An old-fashioned shoot-out here
at the Stanley Cup competition.

852
01:16:25,100 --> 01:16:27,460
Up the alley now,
center circle.

853
01:16:27,500 --> 01:16:29,860
Lines it up to the Penguins.

854
01:16:29,900 --> 01:16:34,260
He'll get the puck out.
He really shakes his stick.

855
01:16:34,340 --> 01:16:38,100
Mike, they're making some noise
down here and I'm not sure why.

856
01:16:38,180 --> 01:16:42,380
I don't believe this. Brad Tolliver
is actually coming back into the game!

857
01:16:42,460 --> 01:16:45,740
This is a guy that once
finished a game with a broken ankle.

858
01:16:51,300 --> 01:16:55,100
Takes a lot of guts to come back in
at this point with Chicago leading, 4-3.

859
01:16:55,180 --> 01:16:58,820
They're on the verge of winning
their first Stanley Cup since 1960.

860
01:16:58,860 --> 01:17:01,220
Now he's just sitting on the bench.

861
01:17:02,460 --> 01:17:04,860
Feeling better?

862
01:17:04,900 --> 01:17:07,300
Then get the fuck in there.

863
01:17:09,700 --> 01:17:12,500
And here he comes.

864
01:17:16,140 --> 01:17:18,980
Now back in goal for Pittsburgh,

865
01:17:19,020 --> 01:17:23,780
number 35, Brad Tolliver,
replacing number 31, Ken Wregget.

866
01:17:23,820 --> 01:17:28,340
I don't know what he did, if he
just recharged his battery or what,

867
01:17:28,460 --> 01:17:32,700
but this guy was really sick
and he's gonna try to finish the game.

868
01:17:32,780 --> 01:17:37,180
Can he can make the big saves to keep
the Penguins within striking distance?

869
01:17:37,260 --> 01:17:40,100
He's got all summer to get better.

870
01:17:40,140 --> 01:17:43,740
There's Tolliver, with the crowd
here literally crazy on their feet.

871
01:17:43,820 --> 01:17:47,580
Penguins looking for a lift here
to try and get back in this game.

872
01:17:47,660 --> 01:17:50,660
Here we go!
Chicago will control the face-off.

873
01:17:50,700 --> 01:17:54,380
- They'll dump it to the Penguin end.
- Stay down there.

874
01:17:54,420 --> 01:17:58,900
- Oh, Christ.
- Chicago drives it back
into Pittsburgh territory.

875
01:17:58,980 --> 01:18:02,500
Chicago slips it back
behind the Pittsburgh goal.

876
01:18:02,580 --> 01:18:06,500
The Penguins try to get the puck back,
and they do just that.

877
01:18:06,580 --> 01:18:09,900
They scramble now
and deliver up the right side.

878
01:18:10,020 --> 01:18:13,820
They have to stay on offense. Tolliver
is not challenging the shooters.

879
01:18:13,900 --> 01:18:16,820
- He hasn't challenged much all night.
- Oh, shit.

880
01:18:20,500 --> 01:18:22,660
Move out!

881
01:18:23,820 --> 01:18:25,540
Move out!

882
01:18:25,620 --> 01:18:28,100
Goddam it, move out!

883
01:18:28,140 --> 01:18:30,340
He's gonna come out.
He'll challenge.

884
01:18:30,340 --> 01:18:35,060
Tolliver hits his head on the ice,
and he's hurt, but play continues.

885
01:18:35,140 --> 01:18:37,860
The puck gets free.
The Penguins have command.

886
01:18:40,140 --> 01:18:42,340
The Penguins trail by only one.

887
01:18:44,100 --> 01:18:48,420
Tolliver hit his head on the ice
so hard his kids will be born dizzy.

888
01:18:55,620 --> 01:18:58,900
This is Chicago on the attack.

889
01:19:26,540 --> 01:19:31,620
What a save by Brad Tolliver!
That's the save of the year!

890
01:19:31,660 --> 01:19:34,580
He oughta get five to ten
for robbing the Hawks on that...

891
01:19:34,660 --> 01:19:36,980
to keep the Penguins within a goal.

892
01:19:37,060 --> 01:19:39,180
Not to mention, Paul,
that he's been sick.

893
01:19:39,300 --> 01:19:43,980
He didn't challenge much this game. Now
he comes up with the save of the year.

894
01:19:44,100 --> 01:19:48,340
No question about it,
that is his biggest save ever.

895
01:20:10,980 --> 01:20:14,780
- He makes a move in front of the net.
- What's he doing?

896
01:20:16,900 --> 01:20:21,060
- He just slammed Dubinsky!
- Tolliver, what the fuck are you doing?

897
01:20:21,100 --> 01:20:24,060
He gave him a right cross
and knocked him down.

898
01:20:24,100 --> 01:20:27,620
He's gonna get
a game misconduct and a fine.

899
01:20:27,660 --> 01:20:30,540
He's put his team shorthanded.
The Penguins now are really in the hole.

900
01:20:30,620 --> 01:20:33,740
Strange night for Tolliver.
I don't know what he's up to.

901
01:20:33,820 --> 01:20:39,500
Tolliver, that's
a thousand-dollar fine!

902
01:20:51,860 --> 01:20:54,340
Get outta the way!

903
01:21:00,220 --> 01:21:01,900
Who the hell are you?

904
01:21:04,220 --> 01:21:05,820
What the hell...

905
01:21:07,700 --> 01:21:10,020
Aaah!

906
01:21:16,940 --> 01:21:20,100
Ysebaert will rebound.
He'll turn and shoot.

907
01:21:20,180 --> 01:21:25,380
Less than three minutes to go. He'll
have to find the puck. And he does.

908
01:21:25,500 --> 01:21:29,140
Face-off.
Off the puck he goes!

909
01:21:29,220 --> 01:21:33,980
Chicago has it back again with two
minutes to go in third-period action.

910
01:21:34,020 --> 01:21:38,060
On the move. The Blackhawks
stopped by the Penguins' line.

911
01:21:45,980 --> 01:21:49,860
The Penguins desperately
trying to get back and tie.

912
01:21:49,940 --> 01:21:53,380
The Chicago Blackhawks
hold on to a 4-3 lead.

913
01:21:53,420 --> 01:21:57,220
Penguins have to look for a big gun
to try and topple Chicago again.

914
01:21:57,260 --> 01:21:59,620
Just moments away, they're gonna pack up
the Stanley Cup and take it to Chicago.

915
01:21:59,660 --> 01:22:01,980
Just moments away, they're gonna pack up
the Stanley Cup and take it to Chicago.

916
01:22:12,260 --> 01:22:15,140
Intercepted by Chicago!

917
01:22:15,220 --> 01:22:18,420
Big check on
John Cullen of the Penguins.

918
01:22:25,300 --> 01:22:30,340
Jagr going for the net, Naslund shoots,
and he's stopped by Belfour.

919
01:22:36,420 --> 01:22:39,260
A minute, thirty-five to go
in the third period.

920
01:22:39,300 --> 01:22:42,420
That's all that remains
for Chicago to win the Stanley Cup.

921
01:22:42,500 --> 01:22:45,340
The Penguins need a rally
to tie the game.

922
01:22:45,420 --> 01:22:47,780
Penguins reach in the corner.

923
01:22:49,260 --> 01:22:52,180
Drop it.

924
01:23:07,660 --> 01:23:10,500
Oh, what a save!

925
01:23:10,540 --> 01:23:14,780
Larmer drills one! Nice stop! He gave
more moves than Mae West on that one!

926
01:23:14,860 --> 01:23:18,540
One minute remaining
in the third period.

927
01:23:18,540 --> 01:23:22,180
And the Penguins
trailing by a goal.

928
01:23:22,220 --> 01:23:24,740
Chicago still
putting pressure on.

929
01:23:26,300 --> 01:23:30,140
Forty seconds remaining now.

930
01:23:31,460 --> 01:23:33,500
Aaah!

931
01:23:34,820 --> 01:23:37,460
The Penguins
need a goal desperately.

932
01:23:37,540 --> 01:23:41,140
Thirty seconds left. Chicago's looking
for the parade down Michigan Ave.

933
01:23:41,220 --> 01:23:43,300
They feel they've got
the Stanley Cup.

934
01:23:48,140 --> 01:23:50,500
Aaah!

935
01:23:59,180 --> 01:24:01,100
Aaah!

936
01:24:01,140 --> 01:24:03,020
...Chicago win the Stanley Cup.

937
01:24:03,060 --> 01:24:06,020
Time again ticking down.
Penguins running out of it.

938
01:24:07,300 --> 01:24:11,620
Penguins reaching for every
possible thing they have.

939
01:24:11,660 --> 01:24:15,460
Chicago takes it away. They'll drive
it to center with 14 seconds to go.

940
01:24:15,460 --> 01:24:17,860
The Penguins don't have much time!

941
01:24:17,900 --> 01:24:20,860
The puck's run by Francis,
ahead to Robitaille.

942
01:24:20,940 --> 01:24:23,540
Not much time to go. Luc Robitaille...

943
01:24:29,780 --> 01:24:33,220
We've got eight seconds left!

944
01:24:37,580 --> 01:24:39,500
Seconds to go.

945
01:24:57,100 --> 01:24:58,980
Stop the press!
Stop the press!

946
01:24:59,020 --> 01:25:00,900
The Penguins have tied the game.

947
01:25:00,940 --> 01:25:05,220
We're going to sudden death overtime!
You would have to be here to believe it!

948
01:25:05,300 --> 01:25:10,180
Lucky Luc has scored for the Penguins
with under a second to go!

949
01:25:14,820 --> 01:25:18,540
This series has been incredible!

950
01:25:18,620 --> 01:25:21,340
- Lucky Luc has done it again!
- Sudden death?

951
01:25:21,380 --> 01:25:23,620
Sudden death.

952
01:25:23,700 --> 01:25:27,340
Paul, the Penguins
would not give up, despite the odds.

953
01:25:27,460 --> 01:25:31,740
Belfour tried everything
in his power to stop them.

954
01:25:31,780 --> 01:25:35,580
The Penguins have forced
sudden death overtime.

955
01:25:35,660 --> 01:25:39,940
The team that scores first in the
next period will win the Stanley Cup!

956
01:25:40,020 --> 01:25:42,340
Pittsburgh goal,

957
01:25:42,460 --> 01:25:45,500
his 14th in the play-offs,
scored by...

958
01:25:45,580 --> 01:25:48,380
Life's just a shitbox
of ironies, huh?

959
01:25:48,460 --> 01:25:51,460
We still got money to move.
I hope it's not mine.

960
01:25:51,540 --> 01:25:53,380
Everybody's got
a little more time.

961
01:25:53,460 --> 01:25:56,300
I'd hate to see them waste it.

962
01:25:56,340 --> 01:25:58,220
Wouldn't you?

963
01:27:33,220 --> 01:27:36,540
Throw away the clocks, because the next
goal is going to win the Stanley Cup.

964
01:27:36,580 --> 01:27:38,460
That's what sudden death
is all about.

965
01:27:38,500 --> 01:27:42,300
Penguins control the draw,
drop it into the Chicago end.

966
01:27:42,380 --> 01:27:44,220
Jagr will carry it in.

967
01:28:59,300 --> 01:29:03,900
Both net-minders coming up tough here.
McEachern has it again!

968
01:29:03,940 --> 01:29:05,820
Psst.

969
01:29:18,620 --> 01:29:20,540
Aah!

970
01:29:21,620 --> 01:29:24,220
Aaaah!

971
01:29:25,580 --> 01:29:28,940
Breaking quickly!
Got a man! Move!

972
01:29:29,020 --> 01:29:32,340
Bang! I'm immortal.

973
01:30:19,780 --> 01:30:21,500
Aah!

974
01:31:24,500 --> 01:31:27,620
Aaaah!

975
01:31:46,700 --> 01:31:49,260
Jagr will carry it in,
but he's checked.

976
01:32:01,500 --> 01:32:04,820
Aaaah!

977
01:32:06,460 --> 01:32:08,660
Holy shit!

978
01:32:16,340 --> 01:32:18,060
What's that?

979
01:33:57,580 --> 01:34:00,380
Daddy!

980
01:34:02,180 --> 01:34:04,620
Daddy.

981
01:34:26,700 --> 01:34:29,380
- Come on, let's go!
- Watch it, will ya?

982
01:34:52,900 --> 01:34:55,260
How many did you find, fireman?

983
01:35:53,660 --> 01:35:55,500
Tyler.

984
01:35:58,220 --> 01:36:01,060
I didn't move, Dad.
I didn't move.

985
01:36:01,100 --> 01:36:03,100
Not even when things
blew up.

986
01:36:03,180 --> 01:36:05,300
I didn't move.

987
01:36:11,300 --> 01:36:13,460
It's over.

988
01:36:17,860 --> 01:36:21,460
You're McCord, right?
I'm Agent Saccio.

989
01:36:21,540 --> 01:36:24,340
Better off not moving
until this settles down.

990
01:36:24,420 --> 01:36:28,180
The Vice President wants very much
to meet you. He's very grateful.

991
01:36:30,820 --> 01:36:32,660
Daddy. Daddy.

992
01:36:32,740 --> 01:36:34,740
Daddy, that's the man.

993
01:36:35,980 --> 01:36:38,180
That's the man, Daddy.
That's him.

994
01:36:44,740 --> 01:36:46,580
Daddy!

995
01:36:52,340 --> 01:36:54,180
Stay with him.

996
01:36:55,340 --> 01:36:57,140
Emily!

997
01:37:01,220 --> 01:37:03,060
Daddy!

998
01:37:16,580 --> 01:37:17,900
Let's go.

999
01:37:29,540 --> 01:37:32,100
Daddy!

1000
01:37:37,740 --> 01:37:39,620
Daddy!

1001
01:37:52,180 --> 01:37:54,500
No!

1002
01:37:54,580 --> 01:37:56,420
Aaah! Daddy!

1003
01:37:57,860 --> 01:38:00,100
Daddy!

1004
01:38:33,860 --> 01:38:37,660
I'm not gonna kill you!

1005
01:38:37,740 --> 01:38:41,500
I'd rather you spent the rest
of your life remembering you
couldn't save your little girl.

1006
01:38:46,180 --> 01:38:47,780
Daddy!

1007
01:39:19,700 --> 01:39:21,620
Aah!

1008
01:39:36,500 --> 01:39:38,180
Aaah!

1009
01:39:40,740 --> 01:39:42,820
Aah!

1010
01:39:55,980 --> 01:39:57,540
Aaah!

1011
01:40:03,780 --> 01:40:06,300
Aaah!

1012
01:40:19,820 --> 01:40:22,340
Aaaah!

1013
01:41:19,780 --> 01:41:22,300
You should've seen my dad.

1014
01:41:23,340 --> 01:41:26,300
My daddy's a fireman.
